data.description: Sweeping Columbia River Views! Historic 1914 Prairie Craftsman, designed by locally renowned architect John Wicks. With river views from nearly every room, this stunning home has been thoughtfully restored, retaining the charm of its' era combined with modern amenities. From the open staircase to the French doors & wood floors, you will be captivated by the period details of this charming home. A remodeled kitchen includes wood cabinetry, SS appliances & a Wolf range. The views are even more impressive upstairs, with a spacious primary bedroom, remodeled full bath & 3 guest bedrooms. A full-height basement allows plenty of room for storage & projects. Enjoy entertaining on the deck & gardening in the back yard. Off-street driveway parking is an added bonus!
